body:
having thought about it a while I think this has limited appeal.

If I want to extend something that extends another I just have to be explicit about it. e.g. in my example above

```
.base {
    ...
}
.component:extend(.base) {
    ...
}
.super:extend(.component, .base) {
    ...
}
```

and for the more complicated cases, perhaps the exact behaviour is difficult to understand.

Well presumably we'll have to solve this anyway:

```
.a:extend(.a) { }
.b:extend(.c) { }
.c:extend(.b) { }
```

Probably you'll need to track the inheritance chain and check on each extend to make sure that no ancestor == self (and self =/= self).
